President Obama issued a statement thanking Ambassador Ron Kirk for his work over the past four years. He acknowledged that Kirk delivered results for the American people and the economy, particularly through trade agreements with Korea, Colombia, and Panama, as well as efforts to open up new markets for American businesses and combat unfair trade practices. Obama praised Kirk's advocacy for the American worker and his belief in the importance of a balanced trade policy for the country's economic future. The President expressed his appreciation for Kirk's service and wished him well.